03832nam a22005655i 9780804772990DE-B159720200723103303.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||200723t20202009cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97808047729907 a10.1515/97808047729902doi  a(DE-B1597)564638  a(OCoLC)1178769826  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 4aN6888.K55W38 2009 7aPHI0010002bisacsh04a760.0921 aWatson, Stephen H., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aCrescent Moon over the Rational :bPhilosophical Interpretations of Paul Klee /cStephen H. Watson. 1aStanford, CA : bStanford University Press, c[2020] 4cÂ©2009  a1 online resource (256 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tList of Figures: Works of Paul Klee -- tAcknowledgments -- tAbbreviations of Frequently Cited Texts -- tIntroduction. Interpreting Klee: Fusing the Architectonic and the Poetic -- t1. On the Withdrawal of the Beautiful -- t2. Gadamer, Benjamin, Aesthetic Modernism, and the Rehabilitation of Allegory -- t3. Of Sartre, Klee, Surrealism, and Philosophy -- t4. Heidegger, Klee's Turn, and the Origin of the Work of Art -- t5. "Fiscourse / D igure" -- t6. The Rapture of Sensuousness -- tNotes -- tIndex 0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWhy, and in what manner, did artist Paul Klee have such a significant impact on twentieth-century thinkers? His art and his writing inspired leading philosophers to produce key texts in twentieth-century aesthetics, texts that influenced subsequent art history and criticism. Heidegger, Adorno, Benjamin, Merleau-Ponty, Lyotard, Sartre, Foucault, Blanchot, Derrida, and Marion are among the philosophers who have engaged with Klee's art and writings. Their views are often thought to be distant from each other, but Watson puts them in conversation. His point is not to vindicate any final interpretation of Klee but to allow his interpreters' different accounts to interact, to shed light on their and on Klee's work, and, in turn, to delineate both a history and a theoretical problematic in their midst. Crescent Moon over the Rational reveals an evolving theoretical constellation of interpretations and their questions (theoretical, artistic, and political) that address and continually renew Klee's rich legacies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aAesthetics, Modernx20th century. 0aAesthetics, Moderny20th century. 0aArt and philosophy. 0aArt criticismxHistoryx20th century. 0aArt criticismxHistoryy20th century. 0aPhilosophy, Modernx20th century. 0aPhilosophy, Moderny20th century. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Aesthetics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804772990zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804772990423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804772990.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles